Durban - eThekwini Fire Department attended to a call out at the Pine Crest Centre in Pinetown after it was reported that smoke was seen in a section of the mall. 
 

 Just before 2pm today, shoppers and staff had to be evacuated from the centre. 

 

 It is alleged that air conditioners in the mall were being serviced. 

 

 According to a source, a rubber ring fell into the compressor, which resulted in the smoke filling up a section of the shopping centre. 
AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
 

 Speaking to the Daily News, Fire Commander for eThekwini West, Alfred Newman, said a team of officers was dispatched to the scene. 

 

 Newman said they managed to out where the smoke was coming from and contained it. 

 

 He said no injuries were reported. 

 

 After checking that the mall was safe, shoppers and staff were allowed back inside and it was business as usual. 

 

 Centre management had not responded to requests for comment at the time of publish.

 

